issue.body:
As most of the developers can't actually fix deprecated code inside external libraries (aside from updating them) it would be nice to respect newly added **quietDeps** flag in library options to silence deprecation warnings from external libraries. 

Would be great to emit a less clogged output from webpack's sass-loader, for example.

```
{
    loader: 'sass-loader',
    options: {
        implementation: require('sass'),
        sassOptions: {
            quietDeps: true
        },
    },
}
```

Thank you
